This is still an experimental coupling.
Only the pelagic BFM is implemented. Remember to use the pelagic configuration
in BFM/General/Configurations

The standard Makefile (Makefile.standard) is provided for future improvements

Required software
- ifort (from version 9.0 upwards)
- svn (subversion client)
- makedepf90 (builds fortran file dependencies)
  http://www.helsinki.fi/~eedelman/makedepf90/makedepf90-2.8.8.tar.gz
  to install:
  tar zxvf makedepf90-2.8.8.tar.gz
  cd makedepf90
  ./configure
  make
  sudo make install

NEMO Source code download:
svn co http://www.bo.ingv.it/svn/nemo/trunk ./nemo-trunk

Input files download
wget http://dodsp.idris.fr/reee512/NEMO/ORCA2_LIM_nemo_v2.tar
rename it to ORCA2_LIM_nemo.tar 

Notes for NEMO compilation on linux
-----------------------------------

1) Prepare the configuration
modeles/UTIL/fait_config ORCA2_LIM_BFM_1D

2) edit the global and local definition
	AA_make.gdef

3) create the AA_make and insert the makefiles
	cd modipsl/modeles/NEMO
	./prep_nemo_linux

IMPORTANT
fait_AA_make is system dependent because based on echo
In this NEMO version I have changed all the echo with print!

NOTES
Added the BFM-related commands of the Makefile to fait_AA_config
Added a new configuration by editing the fait_config and BB_make in ORCA2_LIM_BFM_1D

